title.value: Cross-version Extension `R5.MessageHeader.destination` for use in FHIR R4

description.value: This cross-version extension represents the FHIR R5 element `MessageHeader.destination` for use in FHIR R4.

purpose.value:
This extension is part of the cross-version definitions generated to enable use of the element `MessageHeader.destination` as defined in FHIR R5 in FHIR R4.
The source element is defined as: `MessageHeader.destination` 0..* `BackboneElement`
Across FHIR versions, the element set has been mapped as: * R5: `MessageHeader.destination` 0..* `BackboneElement` * R4B: `MessageHeader.destination` 0..* `BackboneElement` * R4: `MessageHeader.destination` 0..* `BackboneElement`
Following are the generation technical comments: Element `MessageHeader.destination` has is mapped to FHIR R4 element `MessageHeader.destination`, but has no comparisons.

definition.value: The destination application which the message is intended for.

comment.value: There SHOULD be at least one destination, but in some circumstances, the source system is unaware of any particular destination system.
